To the ancients, however, such utterances would have

office of human rulers claims respect: but he also feels im-
placable resentment for a wrong.Benefit thy friends and hurt
thy foes, was the received Greel maxim. Now and again a

nowingly injure any one. But a man might be morally good,
in the ordinary Greel view, and also pious (ej), without
accepting that doctrine: Solon, who was esteemed both, prays
